    <id>tag:www.unboxedconsulting.com,2015-08-25:andrew-white-s-technical-breakfast-club-upgrading-to-rails-5-0-an-overview</id>
    <title>Andrew White’s Technical Breakfast Club: Upgrading to Rails 5.0 - An overview</title>
    <summary type="html">With the impending release of Rails 5.0 likely to be the biggest release
for five years, it&#39;s time to start thinking about migration plans so that
you don&#39;t get left behind.&lt;br/&gt;

[Andrew White](https://www.unboxedconsulting.com/people/andrew-white), Rails Core Team Member and Unboxed&#39;s CTO, is hosting this one-off meetup for &lt;b&gt;Developers&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;Architects&lt;/b&gt;, covering how past major releases have tripped people up and what strategies you need to adopt to make sure your upgrade path is smooth.&lt;br/&gt;

&lt;b&gt;Date:&lt;/b&gt; Wednesday 16th September&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Time:&lt;/b&gt; 09:30 – 10:30 (Breakfast from 09:00)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Location:&lt;/b&gt; 17 Blossom Street, London, E1 6PL&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/andrew-whites-technical-breakfast-club-upgrading-to-rails-50-an-overview-tickets-18313898363?ref=ebtn&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/custombutton?eid=18313898363&quot; alt=&quot;Eventbrite - Andrew White’s Technical Breakfast Club: Upgrading to Rails 5.0 - An overview&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&quot;super_sub_heading&quot;&gt;Andrew will also be covering:&lt;/h2&gt;
• What are the new features in Rails 5.0?&lt;br/&gt;
• What are the minimum requirements to run Rails 5.0?&lt;br/&gt;
• What is the policy for bug fix and security updates once the new Rails 5.0 is released?&lt;br/&gt;
• What legacy features will be removed and no longer supported?&lt;br/&gt;

There will also be a Q&amp;A session afterwards to get any questions out there that you may have about the new upgrade.&lt;br/&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&quot;super_sub_heading&quot;&gt;About Andrew White:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://bit.ly/1ER12kd&quot; alt=&quot;Andrew White&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
Andrew has been a contributor to Rails since 2007 and since 2012 has
been a member of the Rails Core Team responsible for setting the
future direction of the framework. He is currently the only member of
the Core Team based in the UK.&lt;br/&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://bit.ly/1J5QB2v&quot; alt=&quot;Title5&quot;&gt;[pixeltrix](https://github.com/pixeltrix)&lt;br/&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://bit.ly/1dMe7E6&quot; alt=&quot;Title6&quot;&gt;[@pixeltrix](https://twitter.com/pixeltrix)&lt;br/&gt;

