    <id>tag:www.unboxedconsulting.com,2015-07-24:new-government-petitions-website-launched-developed-in-partnership-with-unboxed-consulting</id>
    <title>New government Petitions website launched, developed in partnership with Unboxed Consulting </title>
    <summary type="html">The government and House of Commons has just launched a brand new version of the popular [Petitions](https://petition.parliament.uk) (previously named [e-Petitions](https://www.unboxedconsulting.com/project-stories/e-petitions)) service where members of the public can petition the government and members of parliament on issues that matter to them. The service was redesigned and developed in partnership with a team from Unboxed Consulting. 

&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://bit.ly/1Iat6PV&quot; alt=&quot;Petitions launch&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
([Link to full BBC News article](http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-33599604))

This service is a critical part of e-citizen engagement and offers a unique opportunity for anyone in the UK to gather signatures of support for a specific issue, quickly and simply. It&#39;s part of creating a &lt;i&gt;&quot;new dialogue&quot;&lt;/i&gt; with MPs and ministers. If a petition reaches 10,000 signatures, the government will offer a formal response, and if it reaches more than 100,000 signatures, it will be considered by the newly formed Petitions select committee, for a debate in the House of Commons. The new service is designed to make it as simple as possible to set up a petition - and to sign one about an issue deeply cared about.

&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://bit.ly/1MhF54k&quot; alt=&quot;Petitions&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

This re-launched service is another great example of how the [UK government is leading the world](https://www.unboxedconsulting.com/news/why-plcs-are-looking-to-government-for-digital-inspiration) in digital product development.</summary>
    <link rel="alternate" href="https://www.unboxedconsulting.com/news/new-government-petitions-website-launched-developed-in-partnership-with-unboxed-consulting" />
    <updated>2015-07-24T10:38:00+01:00</updated>
