    <id>tag:www.unboxedconsulting.com,2014-09-08:unboxed-consulting-to-host-event-for-digital-product-leaders</id>
    <title>Distributed development teams fail… now learn ‘new rules’ direct from companies who have created smart, successful and distributed teams</title>
    <summary type="html">&lt;b&gt;9.30am - 12.30pm |  Wednesday 8th October  |  116-120 Goswell Road, London, EC1V 7DP&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;

Digital products require empowered, multi-disciplinary teams work in the same &#39;space&#39; making decisions at the point they are needed. The options for constructing teams are diverse with many permutations of inhouse, outsourced and off/on/nearshoring. And products at different stages of the digital product lifecycle have different needs. 

Key issues: cost, risk, quality, sustainability, speed. No one model ticks all these boxes. So how do we make good choices?

The best companies in the world are creating new formations of teams and applying a common set of rules to enable them to succeed.

&lt;b&gt;Hear the ‘new rules’ from:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
- Paul Westmore – Director of IT, Plymouth University&lt;br/&gt;
- Yoann Martin – Technical Director, notonthehighstreet.com&lt;br/&gt;
- James Tatam - Digital Media Director, Channel 5&lt;br/&gt;
- Richard Stobart - CEO, Unboxed Consulting&lt;br/&gt;
- Steve Lennon - Project Delivery Manager, Unboxed Consulting&lt;br/&gt;

If you are thinking about how to grow your development team or how to get your next product delivered in the most effective way, then this event is for you.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Calling all:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
- Product Owners, Product Managers and Service Managers&lt;br/&gt;
- Managers of digital teams, Delivery Managers and CTOs&lt;br/&gt;
- CEOs of companies scaling new digital products

&lt;b&gt;Join us on Wednesday 8th October to discover:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
1. The right formation of team for your digital product strategy - what are the new options?&lt;br/&gt;
2. The ‘new rules’ to create a distributed team of any format smart and efficient&lt;br/&gt;

